http://www.nascar.com/2007/news/headlines/cup/09/15/jgordon.jjohnson....

I respect Jeff a lot as a racer.  Don't necessarily like him, but have a
great respect for his abilities.  However, he couldn't be more wrong
complaining about the 'erased lead'.  The main goal of the Chase was to
create a 'playoff system', much like the NFL - in fact, to compete directly
against the NFL during the final months of the Nascar season when audiences
would tune out to Nascar and tune in to the NFL if the eventual cup champ
had the championship pretty much 'locked up'.

If Nascar truly wanted a playoff system, then all bets should be off once
the playoffs begin - just like the NFL.  As we all know, you can go 15-1 in
the NFL regular season, and lose to an 8-8 wildcard team in your first
playoff appearance.  Personally, I don't like the chase, but if Nascar
really wants a playoff system, then make it a damn playoff system and let
the best drivers fight it out on equal ground, just like the NFL.
j
