I said it before and I will say it again.  The idea of equalizing the points
for an arbitrary number of drivers was a terribly unfair idea.  It would
have been much more palatable to Jeff Gordon and a great majority of the
fans if NASCAR had simply announced that they were going to double the
traditional points award for the last ten races and call it The Chase.  That
would have added drama and would have given many of the trailing drivers a
way to catch up if they outraced the leading drivers. Admittedly the tenth
place driver who was 400 points back was unlikely to catch the first place
driver but he could certainly improve his position from tenth to fifth if he
raced well towards the end of the season.
