The main goal of the Chase is to subsidize points for mediocre drivers.
Let's call a spade a spade.  NASCAR wants a playoff system without the
playoff format.  Their greed would never allow them to keep the rest of
the field off the track for the last ten races.  There's too many
advertising dollars riding on those cars.

Bowyer got a 572 point gift from NASCAR at the end of race #25 and now
he gets lucky and wins the first Chase race (and his first period) and
is now 15 points out of first place.  If this doesn't prove NASCAR is
promoting mediocrity then nothing will.  This guy shouldn't even be in
the Chase (i.e. he was 637 points out of first) and now he is 15 points
out of first.  What a joke.
