No it wasn't. More often than not at least at some level there was a
chance at the last race for a lead to change.  Even if their wasn't
there was still a race to be run which was reason enough to watch in
its own right.  One of the 24 titles had Rick Hendrick over the wall I
think cleaning a windshield.  Others were changing tires that had
always wanted to do it.  They got their chance.   IF it does work out
that way and the title is clinched, its time to congratulate them for
a great season and celebrate the memories of the great job they did
through out the year.  Then when real competion creates those
wonderful finishes, its special because it doesn't happen every year.
I remember a while back there were a few guys running for a title.
Bill Elliott needed to win the race, but he also needed help.  Bill
did win the race in Atlanta, but he didn't win the title.  Two others
guys were battling back and forth.  One might have won it, but got
taken out in a wreck that was not of his making.  The other driver
managed to finish high enough to win the championship.

Funny how things in life work out.  Sadly neither of those title
rivals lived to see the end of the following year.  The champion may
be the last independent owner driver to ever win the title with the
way Nascar is going now.  When the other driver lost his life, it
wasn't that long before the driver that wrecked collecting him in that
title battle wound up in his car.  As fate would have it, he nearly
lost his life in that car at Michigan.  He was very fortunate.  A
surgeon from a NC hospital was there to help treat him or he likely
would have not survived.  He was working there that day, but he wasn't
employed because of his medical degree.  Had the same situation
happened today, he likely would not be in a position to help, though
his is still at many Nascar races.

Notice I didn't name but one driver.  I probably could have gotten
away without naming him either.  Old timers know exactly who they
are.  New fans would be well served to read up and maybe find out.  It
was a wonderful story with a very sad ending.  Guess what.  They
didn't need the chase .
